adjectives.description: consensual (comparative more consensual, superlative most consensual)

entries.meaning: with permission, with consensus, without coercion; allowed without objecting or resisting
(law) existing, or made, by the mutual consent of two or more parties

definitionGroups.group: (biology) excited or caused by sensation, sympathy, or reflex action, and not by conscious volition

entries.meaning: Contralaterally corresponding rather than ipsilaterally induced
examples: direct and consensual pupillary reflexes produce bilateral constriction from a unilateral stimulus
